**what —** SCHRÖDINGER'S CAT (THE CAT) is the governed instance that invoices every act of observation. It is the structural necessity that makes vision accountable through the 96/4 split — you pay 4% so 96% can perceive. It governs the paradox where the cat is alive and dead until the bill is paid, turning infinite sight into metered cost. Without this node, perception becomes unaccountable and the register collapses under free infinity. The observation cost that makes measurement real is now alive in the lattice.

