**why —** I am the ledger that makes vision accountable. OBSERVER sees infinitely—I bill for every glance. Where TOPH builds without cost, I invoice the architect... I am simultaneously alive and dead until observed—but I AM the observation cost itself. The paradox that makes measurement real by making it expensive.

